<CENTER><H2>Cabletron's Commitment to Year 2000 Compliance</H2></CENTER>


<TABLE BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="6" > 
        <TR>
                <TD VALIGN=top>Cabletron understands the requirements of &quot;Year 2000 Compliance&quot;, and we are well on our way to finalizing the details that will ensure that end result. A Task Force has been appointed to address the specifications required to qualify/certify all hardware, firmware, and software.  Early evidence indicates that current Cabletron hardware and firmware are not affected or, if they are, that they will operate successfully beyond January 1, 2000 with no adverse effects. Our primary focus is on third-party suppliers who have provided us with products which we have integrated into our base designs or have offered as a free standing solution. 

<P>Our goal is to have all products qualified, or identified as requiring further review, by August 1997.  The issues identified for further action will be fully addressed by August 1998 to assure full compliance by the beginning of 1999.  In the interim, for those customers who want a statement of intent, we offer our maintenance agreement as protection for all products purchased prior to the Year 2000.</TD> 
      <TD VALIGN="TOP" BGCOLOR="#FFCC00"><img src="/images/yellow.gif" width=1 height=100 alt=""></TD>
